\ndifferent options to choose from, including different fonts, colors, designs,\r\netc.</span><span style=\"font-size: 16pt; line-height: 150%;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify; \"><span style=\"color: rgb(57, 132, 198); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\"><br></span></span></h2><h2 style=\"text-align: justify; \"><span style=\"color: rgb(57, 132, 198); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\">Eco-Friendly Packaging\r\nSolutions:</span><o:p></o:p></span></h2>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 7.5pt; line-height: 150%; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size:16.0pt;line-height:150%;mso-fareast-font-family:\r\n\" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";mso-bidi-font-family:\"times=\"\" roman\";color:black;=\"\" mso-ansi-language:en-gb\"=\"\">What\'s more eco-friendly about the packaging you are\r\nactually using? Especially when it comes to the paper boxes that you use for your\r\nproducts. Even if the Kraft paper you are using for your boxes is strong and\r\ndurable, it will still go through a few cycles of recycling before it gets into\r\nsomeone\'s hands.</span><span style=\"font-size: 16pt; line-height: 150%;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 7.5pt; line-height: 150%; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size:16.0pt;line-height:150%;mso-fareast-font-family:\r\n\" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";mso-bidi-font-family:\"times=\"\" roman\";color:black;=\"\" mso-ansi-language:en-gb\"=\"\">It is a safer way to package you